CASE SYSTEM (6 cases in Turkish):
- Nominative: subject case, no marker
- Accusative: direct object, -(y)i marker
- Dative: indirect object/direction, -(y)e marker
- Locative: location, -(d)e marker
- Ablative: source/origin, -(d)en marker
- Genitive: possession, -(n)in marker

VOWEL HARMONY RULES:
- Back vowels: a, o, u
- Front vowels: e, ö, ü
- Suffix vowels must harmonize with root's last vowel
- Exceptions: some foreign words, 3rd person plural possessives

WORD ORDER:
- Subject-Object-Verb (SOV) is normal
- Flexible due to case markers
- Question words at sentence beginning

